SIMPLE: knacker
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Knacker
<hw>Knack"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
makes knickknacks, toys, etc.</def> <rj><au>Mortimer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One of two or more pieces of bone or wood held
loosely between the fingers, and struck together by moving the hand; --
called also <altname>clapper</altname>.</def>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Knacker</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Knacker
<hw>Knack"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Icel. <ets>hnakkr</ets> a
saddle.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a harness maker.</def> <mark>[Obs. or
Prov. Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who slaughters worn-out horses and sells their
flesh for dog's meat.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Knackish</ent>⟦br⟧
